securityControls.description:
CMS ARS 5.0 Control: When transferring information between different security domains, the process that transfers information between filter pipelines:
(a) Does not filter message content;
(b) Validates filtering metadata;
(c) Ensures the content associated with the filtering metadata has successfully completed filtering; and
(d) Transfers the content to the destination filter pipeline.<br/><br/>Discussion: The processes transferring information between filter pipelines have minimum complexity and functionality to provide assurance that the processes operate correctly.<br/><br/>Responsibility: System<br/><br/>Priority: P2<br/><br/>

