securityControls.description:
CMS ARS 5.0 Control: (a) Provide a manual override capability for input validation of the information inputs defined in the base control (SI-10); 
(b) Restrict the use of the manual override capability to only CMS defined authorized individuals (defined in the applicable system security/privacy plan); and 
(c) Audit the use of the manual override capability.<br/><br/>Discussion:  In certain situations, such as during events that are defined in contingency plans, a manual override capability for input validation may be needed. Manual overrides are used only in limited circumstances and with the inputs defined by the organization.<br/><br/>Responsibility: System<br/><br/>HVA Control Statement: Â <br/><br/>HVA Discussion: Â <br/><br/>HVA Implementation Standards: Â <br/><br/>

